# Database Schema Mappings & Relationships Reference

This document maps all the database tables, fields, constraints, and relationships for the **Doctor Appointment System**, highlighting the **Credentials-Demographics Separation** and **OTP-based Family Sharing Mappings**.

---

## 1. Table Definitions & Fields

### A. Users
- **Description:** Login credentials and authentication details.
- **Table Name:** `Users`
- **Fields:**
  - `UserId` (Guid, PK)
  - `Email` (string, `VARCHAR(150)`, `NOT NULL`, Unique)
  - `PasswordHash` (string, `VARCHAR(500)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `IsActive` (bool, default `true`)
  - `CreatedDate` (DateTime, default `GETUTCDATE()`)
  - `LastLoginDate` (DateTime, nullable)
  - `RoleId` (Guid, FK -> Roles, Shadow property)

### B. Roles
- **Description:** System authorization roles.
- **Table Name:** `Roles`
- **Fields:**
  - `RoleId` (Guid, PK)
  - `Role` (string, `VARCHAR(50)`, `NOT NULL`) - Enum: `SuperAdmin`, `Admin`, `Doctor`, `Patient`

### C. Patients
- **Description:** Demographic information and clinical profile details. (Independent of credentials, supporting multiple profiles linked to single log-in).
- **Table Name:** `Patients`
- **Fields:**
  - `PatientId` (Guid, PK)
  - `FirstName` (string, `VARCHAR(100)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `LastName` (string, `VARCHAR(100)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `MobileNo` (string, `VARCHAR(20)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `Gender` (string, `VARCHAR(10)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `DOB` (DateTime, `NOT NULL`)
  - `BloodGroup` (string, `VARCHAR(20)`, nullable)
  - `EmergencyConactName` (string, `VARCHAR(100)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `EmergencyConactNumber` (string, `VARCHAR(20)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `CreatedDate` (DateTime, default `GETUTCDATE()`)
  - `UpdatedDate` (DateTime, nullable)

### D. Doctors
- **Description:** Demographic and professional details for care providers.
- **Table Name:** `Doctors`
- **Fields:**
  - `DoctorId` (Guid, PK)
  - `UserId` (Guid, FK -> Users, Shadow property, Unique)
  - `SpecializationId` (Guid, FK -> Specializations, Shadow property)
  - `FirstName` (string, `VARCHAR(100)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `LastName` (string, `VARCHAR(100)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `MobileNo` (string, `VARCHAR(20)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `Gender` (string, `VARCHAR(10)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `DOB` (DateTime, `NOT NULL`)
  - `Qualification` (string, `VARCHAR(150)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `YearsOfExperience` (int, `NOT NULL`)
  - `LicenceNumber` (string, `VARCHAR(50)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `ConsultationFee` (double, `NOT NULL`)
  - `HospitalName` (string, `VARCHAR(150)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `VerificationStatus` (string, default `Pending`)
  - `ProfileImage` (byte[], nullable)
  - `AboutDoctor` (string, `VARCHAR(2000)`, nullable)
  - `CreatedDate` (DateTime, default `GETUTCDATE()`)
  - `UpdatedDate` (DateTime, nullable)

### E. UserPatients (Join Table)
- **Description:** Many-to-Many join table linking `Users` accounts to `Patients` profiles. Used for family access controls and sharing profiles.
- **Table Name:** `UserPatients`
- **Fields:**
  - `UserId` (Guid, PK, FK -> Users)
  - `PatientId` (Guid, PK, FK -> Patients)
  - `RelationshipType` (string, `VARCHAR(50)`, `NOT NULL`) - Enum: `Self`, `Spouse`, `Child`, `Parent`, `Grandparent`, `Sibling`, `Other`
  - `IsVerified` (bool, `NOT NULL`, default `false`)
  - `CreatedDate` (DateTime, default `GETUTCDATE()`)

### F. FamilyVerifications
- **Description:** Temporary OTP records storing pending profile details.
- **Table Name:** `FamilyVerifications`
- **Fields:**
  - `VerificationId` (Guid, PK)
  - `UserId` (Guid, `NOT NULL`, initiator)
  - `MobileNo` (string, `VARCHAR(20)`, `NOT NULL`, target phone)
  - `OtpCode` (string, `VARCHAR(10)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `ExpiresAt` (DateTime, `NOT NULL`)
  - `RelationshipType` (string, `VARCHAR(50)`, `NOT NULL`)
  - `PatientDataJson` (string, `VARCHAR(2000)`, `NOT NULL`)

